 TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Plb.\">Plb.</a></author> </bibl> downwds., <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">τὰ ὕ.</foreign> the <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">field,</tr_> the <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">open country,</tr_> opp. fortified places, <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">τῶν ὑ. ἀντιποιεῖσθαι</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0543.tlg001.perseus-grc1:1:12:4\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1.12.4</biblScope></bibl></cit>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0543.tlg001.perseus-grc1:1:30:6\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1.30.6</biblScope> </bibl>; <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">μάχεσθαι ἐν τοῖς ὑ.</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0543.tlg001.perseus-grc1:18:3:4\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">18.3.4</biblScope> </bibl> </cit>; <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἐκχωρεῖν τῶν ὑ.</foreign> retire from the <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">open country,</tr_> and shut themselves up in the towns, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0543.tlg001.perseus-grc1:9:3:6\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">9.3.6</biblScope> </bibl>; <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">ἡ ἐν ὑπαίθροις οἰκονομία</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0543.tlg001.perseus-grc1:6:12:5\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">6.12.5</biblScope></bibl></cit>. </sense> <sense n=\"3\" id=\"n106816.4\" level=\"3\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἡ ὕπαιθρος</foreign> (sc. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">γῆ</foreign>(, <xr opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"xr\"> <lbl opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"lbl\">=</lbl> <ref targOrder=\"U\" lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"ref\">τὰ ὕπαιθρα</ref></xr>, the <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">field,</tr_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0081.tlg001:8:63\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ D.H.\">D.H.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">8.63</biblScope></bibl>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0081.tlg001:9:6\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">9.6</biblScope></bibl>. </sense> <sense n=\"4\" id=\"n106816.5\" level=\"3\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">open to the sky,</tr_> Lat. <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">hypaethros, aedificia, ambulationes,</tr_> <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Vitr.</author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1.2.5</biblScope></bibl>, <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">5.9.5</biblScope> </bibl>; <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">hypaethros</tr_> (sc. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ϝαός</foreign>), <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">a temple with an open skylight,</tr_> <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Id.\">Id.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">3.2.1</biblScope></bibl>. This form is not used by <gramGrp opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gramGrp\"> <gram type=\"dialect\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gram\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Att.\">Att.</a></gram> </gramGrp> writers except in the phrase <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἐν ὑπαίθρῳ</foreign>; the form employed by them in <pos opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"pos\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Adj.\">Adj.</a></pos> sense is always <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὑπαίθριος</foreign>; <abbr TEIform=\"abbr\">v.</abbr> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0032.tlg003.perseus-grc1:7:20\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ X.\">X.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Oec.\">Oec.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">7.20</biblScope></bibl>, where <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">αἱ ἐν τῷ ὑπαίθρῳ ἐργασίαι</foreign> are sy